<ce:para>This work addresses the scheduling of continuous single-stage multiproduct plants with energy intensive processing tasks and time-dependent electricity cost and power supply. A new rolling horizon algorithm is proposed that consists of a planning model to predict the production levels and a continuous-time model for detailed scheduling. The results from a set of test problems from the literature show that the algorithm can generate global optimal solutions much more rapidly than standalone discrete or continuous-time formulations in problems involving unlimited power availability. Â© 2010 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.</ce:para>
